verbose_text: TMBIM5 / MICS1 (mitochondrial morphology and cristae structure 1)/GHTIM (growth hormone inducible transmembrane protein) is located at the mitochondria, and has been shown to prevent mitochondrial fragmentation and the release of cytochrome c induced by actinomycin D treatment [XREF_BIBR].
